The paper deals with energy optimization in wireless multimedia sensor networks, which is a topic related to networked systems (cs.NI) and information theory (cs.IT). The use of network coding and session scheduling also suggests a possible category of systems and control (cs.SY). The paper specifically focuses on multimedia data, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) and distributed computing (cs.DC) categories.
